<b><br> Sound Bath</b></br>
I went to a spa with my family this weekend. I didn't think I'd like it. I did not relax at all. It was a salt cave and sound bath.
Warm blanket. Eye mask. Chill vibes. My mom said she couldn't chill either. I think it was the audio that did it for me. Very uncomfortable
to sit with some of the frequencies. Definitely not woo woo, but also, full of woo woo at the same time.

It was a terrifying experience to relax in a situation that is designed to take all your senses from you. That is your brain
telling you that this is not okay and I do not accept serenity. I accept reality.

I will have peace when I am dead. Until then, discomfort and sometimes pleasure, but never serenity.

But silencing negative energies through vibrations and sounds? 
Doesn't sound too woo woo to me anymore. 

