<b>The test drive and the test.</b>
I took a test drive and a model Y when I saw when I was with my back against the sun, slowing down for a stop sign. The glare came through the glass and made a cross on the digital display
 and it was a rainbow cross and it was really beautiful and amazing and I only wouldve seen it if I had been there at that moment at that time because my drive got delayed.

But yeah, God said hello with a rainbow during my test drive, so kind of everything else doesnt really matter does it?

When I parked the car because I did self driving a family approached the vehicle and started walking around the vehicle while I was in the car.
It upset me a lot. I asked if they wanted me to move, if I was in their spot, but they circled the car. To other people it would mean nothing. To me, it felt intimidating and scary.
They were looking at the vehicle, not at me. But I have big anxiety around strangers unless they are friendly. There were not normal smiles or things to make me feel at ease, just some people circling the vehicle while I was in it.
It, I think, was meant to be a test to make me look bad because it was a muslim family. People always want you to blame someone's ethnicity so they can pick at your "preconceived bias". OFC. But like, don't circle the vehicle while I"m in it.
I'm a single woman on my own and I trust absolutely no one. Fuck off. Look at the other models on the lot. 

My rough thoughts about it: 
  Why were they walking around the one that I just pulled up in? It made me very uncomfortable. 
  I didnt know how to lock the doors quickly cause I couldnt remember the controls cause its been 
  a while since I was in a Tesla and I think when I rented the model S last, it took me a while to learn the 
  controls too so like I was getting re-oriented its like driving a computer. 
  
  You have to figure out where 
