   People have no idea how fucking difficult is for me to do anything to even fucking be here. Or the mental resilience I've had to build to be able to be in the world again. I have gotten help, and without out, I wouldn't be here.

I am proud of myself for staying calm under pressure, even if I had assistance. I am thankful for the assistance. I am grateful to get another chance to be here, to be in my family's lives, to get to say and write whatever it on my mind
no matter how batshit crazy it sounds and to just spend another day in the sun with the human tribe.
